The paper deals with error control in random network coding, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also involves the study of geometric properties of projective spaces and Grassmannians, which falls under the category of computational geometry (cs.CG) and algebraic geometry (cs.AG). The paper also discusses code design principles, which is related to coding theory (cs.IT) and distributed computing (cs.DC). Finally, the paper involves the study of packing and covering properties of codes, which is related to combinatorics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.DS).
